Nael – Lean for Emacs
*********************

Nael (https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael) is an early-stage package for
GNU Emacs (https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/) providing a minimal and
unobtrusive major-mode for the Lean (https://lean-lang.org/)
programming-language and theorem-prover based on Emacs' built-in
LSP-client Eglot
(https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/eglot/).

   “Nael” is “Lean” reversed and ends in “el” as in Emacs-Lisp.

