2 History
*********

  1. _Microsoft Corporation (R)_ et al.  developed lean4-mode
     (https://github.com/leanprover-community/lean4-mode) based on
     lsp-mode (https://github.com/emacs-lsp/lsp-mode).
  2. _Richard Copley_ developed a fork
     (https://github.com/bustercopley/lean4-mode) based on Emacs'
     built-in Eglot
     (https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/eglot/).
  3. _Mekeor Melire_ developed Nael.  It strives to be unobtrusive and
     minimalist by relying Emacs' built-in facilities, like Eglot, ElDoc
     and Project.



